OL,7,FThroughout the operation, 900 offences
OL,8,Fwere identified, with 41 vehicles
OL,9,Fbeing seized.
OL,11,FSome of those offences discovered
OL,12,Fthroughout the campaign include:
OL,14,FThe force says its operation led to a
OL,15,F53% decrease in collisions they call
OL,16,FKSI, which means killed or seriously
OL,17,Finjured. That reduction has seen
OL,18,Fofficers praised by the national lead
OL,19,Ffor road safety.
